<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Dwedit]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-09-22T09:05:27-07:00</updated>
<published>2011-09-22T09:05:27-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8149&amp;p=84317#p84317</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8149&amp;p=84317#p84317"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Dizzy the Adventurer fixed NSF]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8149&amp;p=84317#p84317"><![CDATA[
The game writes to every sound register every frame.  When it writes to 4000/4004/400C, it sets the "disable envelope" bit, but does not set the "disable length counter" bit.  So you need to hack that along with only writing to 4003/4007/400F if the value has changed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Sep 22, 2011 9:05 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
